Stephens (historian)}}\n* {{cite news | url = https://newspapers.library.wales/view/4334011/4334017/50 | title = The Late Thomas Stephens | year = 1875}}\n* {{cite news | url = https://newspapers.library.wales/view/4334020/4334024/20  | title = The Late Thomas Stephens of Merthyr  | year = 1875}}\n* {{cite news | url = https://newspapers.library.wales/view/3500990/3500993/24  | title = Thomas Stephens  | year = 1875}}\n* [[iarchive:literatureofkymr00steprich/page/n25/mode/2up|The Life of Thomas Stephens. (1876)]]\n* [[iarchive:literatureofkymr00steprich/page/n56/mode/1up|A List of the Mss. Essays and Writings of Thomas Stephens 1876)]]\n* [[iarchive:reddragon00unkngoog/page/n11/mode/2up|Notable Men of Wales. Thomas Stephens. (1882)]]\n* {{cite news | url = https://newspapers.library.wales/view/3108130/3108140/25 | title = Glamorgan  | year = 1905 | quote = portrait of Stephens once in Cardiff Reference Library}}\n* {{cite news | url = https://newspapers.library.wales/view/3434011/3434016/12  | title = Mr Thos. Stephens. Distinguished Welsh Litterateur. Proposed Memorial  | year = 1908}}\n*[[iarchive:eminentwelshmens01robeuoft/page/500/mode/1up/|Stephens, Thomas. (1908)]] (biography)\n*{{cite news | url = https://newspapers.library.wales/view/3435194/3435195/25 | title = Welsh Gleanings | year= 1909 | quote= connections with [[Joseph Edwards (sculptor)|Joseph Edwards]] and [[Charles Wilkins (writer)|Charles Wilkins]]}}\n* {{cite news | url = https://newspapers.library.wales/view/4425461/4425464/35 | title = Neath Valley's Sylvan Spots  | year = 1913 | quote = includes Stephens' birthplace}}\n* {{cite news | url = https://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/wales-news/marble-bust-eminent-welsh-sculptor-11041343  | title = This marble bust by an eminent Welsh sculptor had been left in a cupboard under the stairs at Aberystwyth University  | year = 2016}}\n* {{cite news | url = https://www.wales.ac.uk/en/NewsandEvents/News/CAWCS/Marble-Bust-of-prolific-Merthyr-scholar-rediscover